---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Submit" activePage="submit" description="How to submit a build to The Schematic Archive.">
  <section class="container submit-page">
    <header>
      <p class="eyebrow">Contribute</p>
      <h1>Submit a build</h1>
      <p class="muted">
        Every entry in the Archive starts as a GitHub issue. Maintainers review the submission, then convert it into a PR that adds your folder to the <code>builds/</code> directory.
      </p>
    </header>

    <ol class="steps">
      <li>
        <h3>1. Export your build</h3>
        <p>Use the KindredSchematics in-game command to save your build to a <code>.schematic</code> file. Find it under <code>BepInEx/config/KindredSchematics/</code>.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <h3>2. Take 1 to 6 screenshots</h3>
        <p>At least one wide exterior shot. Optional: interior, throne room, defensive layout, before-and-after with terrain.</p>
        <p class="hint muted">JPG or PNG, ideally 1920px wide or smaller, under 400 KB each. Sharp images, no UI clutter if possible.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <h3>3. Open a Submit Entry issue</h3>
        <p>The issue form asks for everything we need: title, summary, author info, category, tier, modes, DLC packs used, and the schematic file plus screenshots as attachments.</p>
        <p>
          <a class="btn primary" href="https://github.com/Odjit/schematic-archive/issues/new?template=submit-entry.yml">
            Open the Submit Entry form
          </a>
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <h3>4. Wait for review</h3>
        <p>A maintainer will validate the manifest, check the screenshots, and open a PR that adds your entry. You will be tagged on the PR if anything needs a tweak.</p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <h3>5. Once merged, the site updates automatically</h3>
        <p>Deploy runs on every push to <code>main</code>. Your entry typically appears within a few minutes.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Have a build you cannot share through a GitHub form?</strong>
      <p>Drop a comment on the <a href="https://github.com/Odjit/schematic-archive/discussions">Discussions board</a> with a Google Drive or Discord link and we will help get it into the Archive.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .submit-page { padding-top: var(--space-6); padding-bottom: var(--space-7); max-width: 760px; }
  .steps { list-style: none; padding: 0; counter-reset: step; }
  .steps li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-5);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-soft);
  }
  .steps li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .steps h3 { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .hint { font-size: 0.875rem; }
  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    background: var(--color-surface-2);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-soft);
  }
  .callout { margin-top: var(--space-7); }
</style>
